#KarnakTemple dates from around 2055 BC to around 100 ADCult temple dedicated to followers of Amen Ra. It is the largest religious building ever constructed. The temple of #Karnak was known as Ipet-isu—or “most select of places”—by the ancient Egyptians. This temple complex is still capable of overshadowing many wonders of the modern world and in its day must have been awe-inspiring.For the largely uneducated ancient Egyptian population, this could only have been the place of the gods. It is the largest religious building ever made, covering about 200 acres (1.5 km by 0.8 km), and was a place of pilgrimage for nearly 2,000 years.
